```json
[
  {
    "file": "backend/app/services/dryrun_service.py",
    "line": 120,
    "summary": "The try around build_check_runner catches only UnsupportedConnectionTypeError, so a secret-fetch failure during runner build now returns 500 instead of the documented 502.",
    "failure_scenario": "A suite whose connection has a missing/unreadable credential (secret not in Key Vault, or Key Vault unreachable). build_snowflake_runner / build_flatfile_runner call secret_store.get(secret_ref) eagerly at build time and raise (KeyError / vault error). On main this was inside the broad `except Exception -> DryRunFailedError(502)`; now it escapes the narrow except and hits the unhandled-exception handler -> HTTP 500. The docstring explicitly lists 'no credential' as a 502 case, and the existing 502 test only patches run_checks (not the build path), so this regression is uncovered."
  },
  {
    "file": "backend/app/services/dryrun_service.py",
    "line": 139,
    "summary": "materialize_path for a flat-file batch target catches only BatchNotFoundError; any other store-listing failure escapes as a 500 rather than a clean 502.",
    "failure_scenario": "A flat-file batch suite (target `{pattern, strategy}`) whose credential is wrong or whose object store is unreachable. materialize_path -> resolve_batch_file -> list_files performs a live network listing that can raise auth/network exceptions. Only BatchNotFoundError is caught (-> 422); every other exception propagates uncaught -> HTTP 500, contradicting the 'unreachable datasource -> 502' contract. This store-listing step runs before the run_checks try/except, so it is never mapped to DryRunFailedError."
  },
  {
    "file": "frontend/src/components/checks/DryRunPreview.tsx",
    "line": 56,
    "summary": "hasTarget only checks for `table` or `path`, so a flat-file batch suite (target has `pattern`, no table/path) is wrongly gated as non-previewable even though the backend fully supports batch dry-run.",
    "failure_scenario": "User opens the check editor on an S3/ADLS suite whose run target is a batch pattern (e.g. `{pattern: 'orders_(\\d+).csv', strategy: 'latest'}`). targetString(target,'table') and targetString(target,'path') both return undefined, so hasTarget is false, the Dry-run button is disabled, and the reason reads 'Set a table or file target' — even though the suite has a valid, runnable target and the backend would materialize + preview it (or return the clean dry_run_no_data 422). The UI blocks a supported preview."
  }
]
```

